      "True source angles are not specified absolutely; for simulation defaults use symmetric placement around broadside (e.g., -7.5 deg and +7.5 deg) to enforce 15 deg separation.",
      "RMSE-vs-SNR and resolution-threshold results are produced via Monte Carlo simulation with 1000 trials per SNR point.",
      "Resolution limit is defined as the minimum SNR where probability of resolution reaches at least 0.9 under the stated peak-separation rule.",
      "Snapshot support L=200 and M=8 are fixed across SNR sweep unless otherwise specified."
    ]
  }
